    {
      "ESSeqNum": 1,
      "FacilityID": 34532,
      "SummaryText": "hat can by stored at the plant is 8,000 pounds.  There will only be one cylinder (2,000 pounds) on line at any one time.\n\nThe chlorine feed system at the 994 Water plant road facility was constructed in 1991 and is in compliance with all applicable regulation for water treatment facilities.  The emergency back-up cylinder system (4 @ 150 pound) is the only addition to this system.\n\nWe have had no accidental releases of chlorine in the last 5 years.. The automatic vacuum system limits the amount (if any) of chlorine that excapes during operational periods.."
